unitsize(0.6 cm);

int i;

draw(Circle((0,0),1));
label("$\text{Ami}$", dir(180), dir(180));
for (i = 1; i <= 10; ++i) {
  draw(dir(180 - 36*i)--dir(180 - 36*(i - 1)));
}
[/asy]

Ami throws to the fifth girl, then the ball goes to the ninth girl, then to the first girl, then to the fifth girl again, and finally back to Ami.  This takes $\boxed{4}$ throws.
